# Add native dig:// protocol support for the DIG Browser.
#
# Registers the dig:// URL scheme and resolves dig://<urn> resources END-TO-END,
# natively, following the SAME contract as the reference dig-chrome-extension
# and the ecosystem SYSTEM.md ("JSON-RPC 2.0 read methods", "Retrieval key",
# "Merkle inclusion proof", "AES-256-GCM-SIV + HKDF-SHA256"):
#
#   * parse the URN (full urn:dig:<chain>:<storeID>[:<root>]/<resourceKey> form
#     and the dig:// shorthand, with optional ?salt=<hex> for private stores);
#   * retrieval_key = SHA-256(canonical rootless URN);
#   * POST JSON-RPC 2.0 dig.getContent to rpc.dig.net (3 MiB streaming windows);
#   * verify the Merkle inclusion proof against the trusted root;
#   * derive the per-URN AES-256 key (HKDF-SHA256) and decrypt AES-256-GCM-SIV;
#   * render the verified + decrypted bytes (fail-closed on any tamper/decoy).
#
# The native crypto (net/url_request/dig_crypto.cc) is a byte-for-byte C++ port
# of digstore-core (crypto.rs / merkle.rs / urn.rs) using BoringSSL, so it stays
# byte-identical to the dig_client WASM the extension/hub/digstore share.

